- Fix site 3 is load-bearing. `wait_for_idle()` calls `database_has_pending_projection_work()` directly, while terminal rows are only created for queued projection outcomes; after rebuild deletes terminals, the pending probe must also skip invalidated edges or `drain()` can see phantom pending work.
- The test drives the real `consolidate_with_provider` path, not a direct `t_invalid` update, and checks both FTS and vec exclusion while proving the valid edge survives. Refs: [rebuild_projections.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.12-sliceA/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/rebuild_projections.rs:308), [rebuild_projections.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.12-sliceA/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/rebuild_projections.rs:331).
- Nodes are untouched, and the existing `superseded_at IS NULL` distinction remains intact.

I did not run tests because this session is read-only; from inspection, the new test would fail without the FTS/vec rebuild predicates, and would hang/fail at `drain()` without the pending-work probe predicate.
